INSERT INTO `crp_indicator_reports` VALUES ('398', '10', null, '7', '1. CSA Profiles: http://dapa.ciat.cgiar.org/csa-profiles\r\n2. Participatory video is a framework for participatory research with a gender focus: blog: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/es/blog/j%C3%B3venes-de-nicaragua-cuentan-su-historia-trav%C3%A9s-de-videos-participativos#.VOdaBS5BZhk\r\n3. In Cauca, Colombia we are working with Ecohabitats, a local organization, on Local Adaptation Planning with a Gender Focus; a presentation was made at CIAT in 2014 explaining the concept.  http://ccafs.cgiar.org/taller-manejando-el-clima-desde-la-vereda#.VOdZ0S5BZhk\r\n4. Climate smart agriculture rapid appraisal (CSA-RA): A prioritization tool for outscaling CSA is a framework that was developed during the implementation of an IFAD-funded project in East Africa.  blog: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/simple-yet-comprehensive-climate-smart-agriculture-rapid-appraisal-prioritization-tool#.VOdZdC5BZhk  \r\n5. We are also using the concepts of gender inequalities to guide quantitative, sex-disaggregated data collection in various CCAFS sites.  The CCAFS gender survey, Phase 2 was developed by CIAT and partners using this framework to collect sex-disaggregated data about perceptions of climate change, awareness and adoption of CSA practices, access to information, access/control of factors of production, decision-making, division of labor, etc., which allows us to understand the potential ways gender differences influence adaptation to climate change and how different CSA practices might impact gender differences.\r\n6. http://ciat.cgiar.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/policy_brief_global_diets.pdf\r\n7.LivestockPlus Concept: Livestock Plus strategic inititaive. Part of CIAT’s strategy. http://ciat.cgiar.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CIAT_Strategy_2014_2020.pdf                           Publication of 2 issues of Tropical Grasslands-Forrajes Tropicales: http://www.tropicalgrasslands.info/index.php/tgft. Worldwide 46,333 visitors of the website Jan-Sep 2014', '', '13', '1', '2014', '2014-01-28 19:41:02');
