INSERT INTO `crp_indicator_reports` VALUES ('1032', '4', null, '5', '1) CSA-Plan: \r\n- Presentation made at the CSA Global conference in Montpellier: http://www.slideshare.net/cgiarclimate/l21-csa-conference-campbell-et-al-csa-plan-316final?qid=9cc2cdc2-c0ad-41f3-9c60-d21167010e31&v=qf1&b=&from_search=24\r\n- Poster: https://www.dropbox.com/s/0een0fnqjo6eqlk/CSA-Plan%20Poster1.pdf?dl=0 \r\n- Video on the Prioritization framework: https://www.powtoon.com/show/b0JHzjnt6LT/csa-prioritization-framework/#/\r\n- Guidebook Participatory Process under developement\r\n- Blog post: Prioritization pilot in Mali: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/climate-smart-solutions-mali#.VSMFp5OxjLk\r\n- Blog post:  Creating a \'learning center\' for agricultural development in Guatemala: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/creating-learning-center-agricultural-development-guatemala#.VSMF_ZOxjLk\r\n\r\n\r\n2) Country profiles in LAC with WorldBank : Profiles for 7 countries were jointly produced with the CIAT team and presented to the Worldbank and external audiences during 2014.  \r\n- See more at: http://www.ciatnews.cgiar.org/2014/10/30/country-profiles-on-climate-smart-agriculture-well-received-at-the-world-bank/#sthash.0AxqfKl5.dpuf\r\n- http://dapa.ciat.cgiar.org/csa-profiles/\r\n- http://ccafs.cgiar.org/research-highlight/new-latin-america-country-profiles-open-pathways-reaching- climate-smart#.VOdaofmG9LE\r\n- http://ciatblogs.cgiar.org/support/world-bank-smart-investments-in-triple-win-agriculture/\r\n- http://climate-l.iisd.org/news/ciat-catie-produce-lac-climate-smart-agriculture-profiles/ \r\n\r\n3) Climate Analogue Tool:  http://www.ccafs-analogues.org/tool/ \r\n- Climate Analogues Tool explanatory video:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f9C1RpV6ta0\r\n- Blog posts: \r\n•Climate scenarios and analogues: A glimpse into past, present and future climates.\r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/climate-scenarios-and-analogues-glimpse-past-present-and-future-climates \r\n•Reaching the private sector with tools and resources for climate-smart agriculture in East Africa\r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/reaching-private-sector-tools-and-resources-climate-smart-agriculture-east-africa\r\n•Improving adaptation planning in Tanzania through the climate analogue tool: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/improving-adaptation-planning-tanzania-through-climate-analogue-tool \r\n•Farmers from climate-smart villages in Lower Nyando and Kericho can now identify adaptive measures for future climate: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/farmers-climate-smart-villages-lower-nyando-and-kericho-can-now-identify-adaptive-measures \r\n•Magic glue or sticking point? Linking land use and climate change through National Adaptation Plans: http://www.landscapes.org/magic-glue-sticking-point-linking-land-use-climate-change-national-adaptation-plan/  \r\n•Sustainable agriculture: “Bridging the knowledge gap between farmers and scientists”:\r\nhttp://blog.cimmyt.org/sustainable-agriculture-bridging-the-knowledge-gap-between-farmers-and-scientists-alertnet/ \r\n\r\nTheses & Reports citing the Analogue approach:\r\n• Vermeulan S and Wynter A. Working with farmers for agricultural innovation and climate adaptation. 2014. CCAFS Working Paper no. 77. CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS). Copenhagen, Denmark. Available online at: https://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/41812/Working%20with%20Farmers%20CCAFS%20WP77.pdf \r\n• Jarvis A. , Ramirez-Villegas J. , Nelson V. , Lamboll R. , Nathaniels N., Radeny M., Mungai C., Bonilla-Findji O., Arango D. and Peterson C. (2014). Farms of the Future: an innovative approach for strengthening adaptive capacity on International Workshop on Agricultural Innovation Systems in Africa (AISA). Available at: http://r4d.dfid.gov.uk/pdf/outputs/ccafs/Innovation_in_Smallholder_Africa_Proceedings.pdf#page=126\r\n• Tyagi NK, Joshi PK, Aggarwal PK, Khatri-Chhetri A. 2014. Institutions and Policies to Scale Out Climate-Smart Agriculture: South-South Exchanges. CCAFS Workshop Report. Copenhagen, Denmark: CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS): https://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/41813/Workshop%20Report%20Colombo%202013.pdf \r\n• Sunil Archak, DP Semwal, Sushil Pandey and BS Phogat (2014). Utilization of ex situ collections and climate analogues for enhancing adaptive capacity to climate change: Final Report. National Bureau of Plant Genetic Resources, New Delhi. India. pp. 47. Available online at: http://www.nbpgr.ernet.in:8080/climate/images/NBPGR_CCAFS_report.pdf \r\n\r\nPeer-reviewed articles citing the analogue apporoach:\r\n• Bellard, C., Leclerc, C., Leroy, B., Bakkenes, M., Veloz, S., Thuiller, W. and Courchamp, F. (2014), Vulnerability of biodiversity hotspots to global change. Global Ecology and Biogeography, 23: 1376–1386. doi:10.1111/geb.12228. Available at: http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/geb.12228/abstract\r\n• Bizikova L, Echeverría D, Hammill A. 2014. Systematic review approach to identifying key trends in adaptation governance at the supranational level. CCAFS Working Paper no. 93. Copenhagen, Denmark: CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS). Available at:\r\nhttps://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/51831/CCAFS_WP93.pdf \r\n• Jost C, Sebastian L 2014. Workshop on Mapping out a CCAFS R4D Agenda and Strategy for Southeast Asia. CGIAR Research Program on Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS). Copenhagen, Denmark: https://cgspace.cgiar.org/bitstream/handle/10568/35586/Workshop%20on%20Mapping%20out%20a%20CCAFS%20R4D%20Agenda.pdf \r\n• Nyairo R., Onwonga R. , Cherogony K., Luedeling E. (2014), Applicability of Climate Analogues for Climate Change Adaptation - Planning in Bugabira Commune of Burundi. Published by Canadian Center of Science and Education, ISSN 1927-050X E-ISSN 1927-0518, Sustainable Agriculture Research; Vol. 3, No. 4; 2014.http://www.ccsenet.org/journal/index.php/sar/article/viewFile/38493/22632\r\n• Beniston M., European Isotherms Move Northwards By Up To 15 Km/Year: Using Climate Analogues For Awareness-Raising, European Scientific Journal May 2014 /SPECIAL/ edition ISSN: 1857 – 7881 (Print) e - ISSN 1857- 7431. Available at: \r\nhttp://www.eujournal.org/index.php/esj/article/viewFile/3313/3095\r\n\r\nBriefs:\r\n• CCAFS. 2014 Herramientas y Métodos para la Planeación y Toma de Decisiones en Agricultura y Cambio Climático. Copenhagen, Denmark: CGIAR Research Programo n Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security (CCAFS)\r\nhttp://issuu.com/cgiarclimate/docs/tools_approaches_booklet \r\n•Nyando farmers on a climate journey to spur adaptation to climate change.\r\nhttp://reliefweb.int/report/kenya/nyando-farmers-climate-journey-spur-adaptation-climate-change \r\n•Cambio Climático, Agricultura y Seguridad Alimentaria  “Herramientas y Métodos para la Planeación y Toma de Decisiones en Agricultura y Cambio Climático” Dirk Hoffmann.\r\nhttp://www.cambioclimatico-bolivia.org/pdf/cc-20141204-Cambio_Cli___.pdf \r\n\r\n\r\n4) Agimpacts: Development of a living database and portal of climate impacts on crops for prioritizing adaptation priorities. \r\n- http://ag-impacts.org\r\n\r\n5) Systemic Framework for Integrated Adaptation Planning\r\n- http://ccafs.cgiar.org/systemic-integrated-adaptation#.VSL605OxjLk\r\n- Three CCAFS Working Papers and 3 journal articles came out of this work.  The working papers included: \r\n• Deconstructing Local Adaptation Plans for Action (LAPAs) - Analysis of Nepal and Pakistan LAPA initiatives; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/publications/deconstructing-local-adaptation-plans-action-lapas-analysis-nepal-and-pakistan-lapa#.VSMHwZOxjLk\r\n• Climate Change Adaptation Policy in Ghana: Priorities for the Agriculture Sector; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/publications/climate-change-adaptation-policy-ghana-priorities-agriculture-sector#.VSMH2pOxjLk\r\n• Systemic Integrated Adaptation: Community Diagnostic, Prioritization and Planning Toolkit: A guidebook for researches and adaptation practitioners working with local communities (in review)\r\n* Series of power/influence mapping reports in Central America: See for Guatemala: http://ccafs.cgiar.org/node/38546#.VOJzZC6xjLk', '', '2', '1', '2014', '2014-02-19 17:19:57');
