INSERT INTO `crp_indicator_reports` VALUES ('1145', '150', null, '150', '* Analogues trainings in Tanzania, Kenya and Peru:: \r\n-  Generando Oportunidades con el Cambio Climático, Sierra Exportadora, Gobierno de Perú: http://www.sierraexportadora.gob.pe/foro/general-group2/todos-forum2/generando-oportunidades-con-el-cambio-clim%C3%A1tico-thread4.0/\r\n- Climate scenarios and analogues: A glimpse into past, present and future climates.\r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/climate-scenarios-and-analogues-glimpse-past-present-and-future-climates \r\n- Improving adaptation planning in Tanzania through the climate analogue tool\r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/improving-adaptation-planning-tanzania-through-climate-analogue-tool \r\n- Farmers from climate-smart villages in Lower Nyando and Kericho can now identify adaptive measures for future climate\r\nhttp://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/farmers-climate-smart-villages-lower-nyando-and-kericho-can-now-identify-adaptive-measures \r\n\r\n* SIA work:\r\n- The SIA workshop methodology was integrated into a UNEP World Conservation Monitoring Center (WCMC) program in West Africa. The social lens researcher traveled to Senegal and Gambia to train public servants on the use of the methodology in June and July 2014. The program also adopted the SIA strategy to provide seed funding to Gambian and Senegalese communities based on the strategic plan coming out of the participatory workshop. Ongoing management support to these programs in both countries. The manual outlining the methodology was also translated into French for use throughout French-speaking West Africa. \r\n- The social lens researcher presented results at the Anthropocene Campus of the Haus der Kulturn der Welt (HKW) in Berlin in November 2014. She also delivered a departmental lecture outlining the social lens results on nutritional status and adaptive capacity in November 2014.\r\n- Colombian students enrolled in the course Climate change and agricultural biodiversity, Universidad Nacional de Palmira:http://sia.palmira.unal.edu.co/buscador/service/asignaturaInfo.pub?plan=&cod_asignatura=5008601.  \r\n\r\n- Ecocrop training workshop held at IIAM Mozambique.\r\n- Participatory trials and 7 training sessions for target communities from Chicualacuala and Xai-Xai districts on agro processing knowledge and techniques for vegetables, roots, tubers and fruits.', '', '2', '12', '2014', '2014-02-24 14:43:17');
