INSERT INTO `crp_indicator_reports` VALUES ('1427', null, null, '3', '* Climate Analogue \r\n\r\n* Ecocrop \r\n\r\n*  Improvement of the Cassava crop modell into DSSAT and set up strategies towards the development of a robust crop model applicable under a variety of scenarios, including climate change.\r\n\r\n* Climate Analogue Tool: Further tool developemnt and wide capacity building activities carried out in EA, WA and Latin America (www.analogue.org; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/east-africa-moves-towards-implementation-plans-using-climate-analogues-tool AP178; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/creating-needed-capacity-use-climate-information-ethiopia; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/climate-change-models-may-help-spur-lawmakers-implement-seed-treaty; http://ccafs.cgiar.org/blog/climate-analogues-arrives-costa-rica-time-pgr-conservation).\r\n- Climate Analogue Training Manual by Flora Mer, Julian Ramirez-Villegas, Osana Bonilla-Findji, David Arango, Camilo Barrios, Ousmane Ndiaye, Andy Jarvis (available upon request).\r\n- Explanatory Video : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZlWznCElKME\r\n\r\n* Parameterization of the Ecocrop model: Calibration made for several globally important food crops using observed crop and climate data and expert knowledge.  Those crop include among others:  Beans, Cowpeas, Groundnuts, Plaintains/banana, Potatoes,  Sorghum, Cassava, Sweet potatoes, Yams, Millet\r\nBarley, Maize, Pigeonpeas, Wheat\r\n\r\n* Rethinking a Cassava crop model :\r\n- development of new module (Phisiological processes) within the DSSAT umbrella out from the original CROPSIM-Cassava module.\r\n http://dapa.ciat.cgiar.org/rethinking-a-cassava-crop-model/\r\nhttp://dapa.ciat.cgiar.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/rethinking-cassava-model.pdf', '', '2', '4', '2012', '2014-02-28 15:14:54');
